<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="1463477">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>You're kind of thinking about it backwards.  Any file that will use the session object will need to include the file containing that class definition.  The alternative is to use __autoload to pull the class in:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">__autoload</span>(<span class="hljs-params"><span class="hljs-variable">$classname</span></span>)
</span>{
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (<span class="hljs-variable">$classname</span> == <span class="hljs-string">'Session'</span>)
  {
    <span class="hljs-keyword">include_once</span> <span class="hljs-string">'Session.php'</span>;
  }
}
</code></pre>

<p>EDIT : you'll need to put the file containing that autoload into every file that will use it.</p>
    </div>
